  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════
       THEMATIC READING PATHS
       ══════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="reading-paths-section" aria-label="Thematic reading paths">
    <div class="reading-paths-heading">Guided Reading Paths</div>
    <h2 class="reading-paths-title">Three ways to cross the archive without reading it straight through.</h2>
    <p class="reading-paths-copy">If you would rather follow a theme than a chronology, these paths hold the family together by inheritance, voice, and recurrence.</p>
    <div class="reading-paths-grid">

      <div class="reading-path-card">
        <span class="reading-path-icon">✦</span>
        <div class="reading-path-title">Follow the Women</div>
        <p class="reading-path-desc">Four women across nine centuries who held the line when the men around them could not.</p>
        <ul class="reading-path-stops">
          <li><a href="era-I.html">Vol. I — Aelswith</a></li>
          <li><a href="era-II.html">Vol. II — Matilda</a></li>
          <li><a href="era-VI.html">Vol. VI — Augusta</a></li>
          <li><a href="era-X.html">Vol. X — Eleanor</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="reading-path-card">
        <span class="reading-path-icon">⚖</span>
        <div class="reading-path-title">Follow the Land</div>
        <p class="reading-path-desc">The Hale holding — how it was won, kept, tested, and passed on across every upheaval England could produce.</p>
        <ul class="reading-path-stops">
          <li><a href="era-I.html">Vol. I — The grant</a></li>
          <li><a href="era-III.html">Vol. III — The Dissolution</a></li>
          <li><a href="era-IV.html">Vol. IV — The Civil War</a></li>
          <li><a href="era-IX.html">Vol. IX — New Towns</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="reading-path-card">
        <span class="reading-path-icon">✉</span>
        <div class="reading-path-title">Follow the Letters</div>
        <p class="reading-path-desc">The Hale voice across the centuries — how this family wrote to each other, and what they chose to say.</p>
        <ul class="reading-path-stops">
          <li><a href="era-III.html">Vol. III — William to his father</a></li>
          <li><a href="era-IV.html">Vol. IV — John &amp; Thomas</a></li>
          <li><a href="era-VI.html">Vol. VI — Augusta's letters</a></li>
          <li><a href="era-VIII.html">Vol. VIII — Thomas's telegrams</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="feedback-prompt" aria-label="Reader feedback">
    <div class="feedback-card">
      <h3 class="feedback-head">Help shape the next revision</h3>
      <p class="feedback-sub">Was this clear so far? What confused you most? This helps improve the reading path for new visitors.</p>
      <form id="archiveFeedbackForm">
        <div class="feedback-choice-row">
          <label>
            <input type="radio" name="feedback_clarity" value="clear" checked>
            <span class="feedback-choice">Clear</span>
          </label>
          <label>
            <input type="radio" name="feedback_clarity" value="mostly_clear">
            <span class="feedback-choice">Mostly clear</span>
          </label>
          <label>
            <input type="radio" name="feedback_clarity" value="confusing">
            <span class="feedback-choice">Confusing</span>
          </label>
        </div>
        <textarea id="feedbackConfusion" name="feedback_confusion" maxlength="700" placeholder="What was unclear, confusing, or hard to follow?"></textarea>
        <div class="feedback-actions">
          <button type="submit" class="feedback-submit">Submit feedback</button>
          <span class="feedback-status" id="feedbackStatus" aria-live="polite"></span>
        </div>
      </form>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════
       ARCHIVE SEARCH — The discovery begins here
       ══════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="search-section">
    <div class="search-panel">
      <div class="search-heading">Search the Archive</div>
      <h2 class="search-title">Enter by person, place, object, or the fragment that stayed with you.</h2>
      <p class="search-copy">The record is broad enough to browse and strange enough to search. If a name, date, phrase, or image catches, this is the quickest way back into the line.</p>
      <div class="search-bar-wrap">
        <span class="search-icon">⌕</span>
        <input type="text"
               id="archiveSearch"
               placeholder="Search by name, date, event, or document type..."
               autocomplete="off"
               spellcheck="false"
               aria-label="Search the Hale-Marsh archive">
        <span class="search-shortcut">/ to focus</span>
      </div>
      <div class="search-hint">Try: <span>Voss</span> &nbsp;·&nbsp; <span>plague</span> &nbsp;·&nbsp; <span>telegram</span> &nbsp;·&nbsp; <span>confession</span> &nbsp;·&nbsp; <span>pig</span> &nbsp;·&nbsp; <span>Matilda</span></div>
      <div class="search-results" id="searchResults" role="region" aria-live="polite"></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="archive-instruction">
    <div class="section-kicker">By Era</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Or enter through the volumes themselves, with the archive guiding your first steps.</h2>
    <p class="section-copy">Not every volume is equally useful on a first visit. The opening chronicle is the cleanest beginning, the next books deepen the family line, and the rest of the archive opens more fully once the record has taken shape.</p>
  </div>

  <main class="archive-clusters">
    <section class="archive-cluster archive-cluster--start" aria-label="Start here in the volumes">
      <div class="archive-cluster-head">
        <div class="archive-cluster-kicker">Start Here</div>
        <p class="archive-cluster-copy">Begin with the founding document and let the archive teach you how it wants to be read.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="archive-cluster-grid">

    <a class="archive-box archive-box--feature" href="era-I.html">
      <span class="archive-box-badge">Best first volume</span>
      <div class="box-spine" style="background:#8B1A1A"></div>
      <div class="box-banner">
        <img src="banners/era-I.jpg" alt="" style="object-position:center 30%;">
        <div class="box-banner-overlay"></div>
        <div class="box-banner-vol">VOL. I  ·  1066–1121</div>
      </div>
      <div class="box-label">
        <div class="box-vol">Vol. I &nbsp;·&nbsp; 1066–1121</div>
        <div class="box-title">The Chronicle of<br>de la Hale</div>
        <div class="box-dates">1066 — 1121</div>
        <div class="box-divider"></div>
        <div class="box-desc">Norman England. Brother Eadmer's chronicle. The founder's question. Edwin the Saxon at Hastings.</div>
        <span class="box-enter">Open box →</span>
      </div>
      <!-- Norman sword -->
      <div class="box-era-art"><svg width="36" height="54" viewBox="0 0 36 54"><line x1="18" y1="2" x2="18" y2="46" stroke="#C8A83C" stroke-width="2.5"/><line x1="6" y1="16" x2="30" y2="16" stroke="#C8A83C" stroke-width="2.5"/><polygon points="18,46 14,53 22,53" fill="#C8A83C"/><rect x="15" y="43" width="6" height="3" fill="#C8A83C"/></svg></div>
    </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="archive-cluster archive-cluster--continue" aria-label="Continue here after the opening">
      <div class="archive-cluster-head">
        <div class="archive-cluster-kicker">Continue Here</div>
        <p class="archive-cluster-copy">Once Vol. I has oriented you, these volumes carry the family from <strong>origin</strong> into <strong>inheritance</strong> and then into the first unmistakable patterns that will echo through the rest of the archive.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="archive-cluster-grid">

    <a class="archive-box archive-box--continue archive-box--feature" href="era-II.html">
      <span class="archive-box-badge">Next after Vol. I</span>
      <div class="box-spine" style="background:#5C3A1E"></div>
      <div class="box-banner">
        <img src="banners/era-II.jpg" alt="" style="object-position:center 30%;">
        <div class="box-banner-overlay"></div>
        <div class="box-banner-vol">VOL. II  ·  1121–1400</div>
      </div>
      <div class="box-label">
        <span class="archive-box-note">The line becomes a house</span>
        <div class="box-vol">Vol. II &nbsp;·&nbsp; 1121–1400</div>
        <div class="box-title">The House of Hale</div>
        <div class="box-dates">1121 — 1400</div>
        <div class="box-divider"></div>
        <div class="box-desc">The family settles into inheritance, weather, death, marriage, and recurrence. This is where the line first starts to feel lived in.</div>
        <span class="box-enter">Open box →</span>
      </div>
      <!-- Plague cross -->
      <div class="box-era-art"><svg width="38" height="50" viewBox="0 0 38 50"><rect x="16" y="2" width="6" height="46" fill="#8B1A1A"/><rect x="2" y="14" width="34" height="6" fill="#8B1A1A"/></svg></div>
    </a>

    <a class="archive-box archive-box--continue" href="era-III.html">
      <span class="archive-box-badge">Then deepen the line</span>
      <div class="box-spine" style="background:#7A1C1C"></div>
      <div class="box-banner">
        <img src="banners/era-III.jpg" alt="" style="object-position:center 30%;">
        <div class="box-banner-overlay"></div>
        <div class="box-banner-vol">VOL. III  ·  1485–1560</div>
      </div>
      <div class="box-label">
        <span class="archive-box-note">The record begins to fracture</span>
        <div class="box-vol">Vol. III &nbsp;·&nbsp; 1485–1560</div>
        <div class="box-title">The Hale Inheritance</div>
        <div class="box-dates">1485 — 1560</div>
        <div class="box-divider"></div>
        <div class="box-desc">Religion, law, and family memory begin pulling against one another. The archive becomes more conflicted, and more recognizably Hale.</div>
        <span class="box-enter">Open box →</span>
      </div>
      <!-- Tudor rose — 5 petals -->
      <div class="box-era-art"><svg width="48" height="48" viewBox="0 0 48 48"><circle cx="24" cy="24" r="7" fill="#7A1C1C"/><ellipse cx="24" cy="8" rx="5" ry="9" fill="#7A1C1C" opacity="0.85"/><ellipse cx="24" cy="8" rx="5" ry="9" fill="#7A1C1C" opacity="0.85" transform="rotate(72 24 24)"/><ellipse cx="24" cy="8" rx="5" ry="9" fill="#7A1C1C" opacity="0.85" transform="rotate(144 24 24)"/><ellipse cx="24" cy="8" rx="5" ry="9" fill="#7A1C1C" opacity="0.85" transform="rotate(216 24 24)"/><ellipse cx="24" cy="8" rx="5" ry="9" fill="#7A1C1C" opacity="0.85" transform="rotate(288 24 24)"/><circle cx="24" cy="24" r="4" fill="#F5EDD6" opacity="0.3"/></svg></div>
    </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="archive-cluster archive-cluster--later" aria-label="Read later or use as advanced entry points">
      <div class="archive-cluster-head">
